USA: Repetition is Mother of Wisdom
It becomes even comical, the assiduous effort with which Barack Obama, president with the reputation of a wise, reproduces his predecessor’s strategy on the Afghan issue, which he himself regarded as quite simple.
When he eventually let his doctrine sweat so much awaited, it turned out that he had copied it on carbon paper since Bush’s Iraqi scenario three years ago.
Not content with using in the text even several times the expression "as in Iraq", he did not hesitate, moreover, to use the title of Bush's January 2007 speech as the title of his own speech: "A new road forward."
At the same time, he personally criticized Bush’s idea of sending new reinforcements into an Iraq consumed by the civil war as being “irresponsible and a catastrophic decision in its consequences.”
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, which came from the recommendations of campaign commanders, was the only possible and likely to be successful to such an extent that at present the newspapers are not talking about Iraq at all.
This did not improve Bush's reputation, that said, objectively speaking, he left his successor a much more favorable final situation than could be expected.
Barack Obama hopes the miracle will happen again in Afghanistan
Again, it was the campaign commanders who asked him to increase the military contingent, including the commander of the Afghan operation, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the White House's reluctance despite the habits of subordination.
He asked for 40,000 men to make the situation more favorable.
The president hesitated for three months, but in the absence of a better option, he scammed at least the general of 10,000 soldiers.
It managed to remove the promise of an additional 5,000 from Europe, even though it originally had 10,000.
What brings the most problems in the entire Obama strategy seems to be his intention to withdraw the armies from Afghanistan within 18 months and complete this whole process within three years.
Many doubt that a half increase will bring the same fruit as the increase in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honor the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan stands out from the exact opposite - no one can be counted on and no treaty is respected.
In these circumstances, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, accustomed to changing leaders day-to-day according to their convenience.
Political institutions, although officially founded, will remain only dust in the eyes behind which patriarchal ethnic relations will proliferate.
It is singularly complex to balance the interests of the various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity in relations, which are still complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "fast-to-act state", which is the core purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The time horizon of Obama's strategy makes him perplexed by his volunteerism.
In the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only worsened and is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a purely romantic and out-of-reality heart can be persuaded that the little soldiers sent into the tumult of war in order to "come home soon" will bring a real miracle there.
From a political point of view, setting a date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible since the Taliban will consider it as an indirect confession to the US defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that Europeans’ willingness to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is oriented towards the negative.
European politicians do not know and do not want to explain to their voters how security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the Hindu Kush Mountains.
Another factor that can radically alter the situation is the evolution of Iran-related events.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the strengthened sanctions have no effect on Iranians, the Americans will face the very difficult issue of solving the problem by using military force.
It will have to be answered, for example, when, according to Obama, America will come to the victorious withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each such solution will result in a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only rusticity for Obama is the fact that there are three years left until the presidential elections and therefore there is still enough time for him to work on a new strategy, in case it proves to be a total fiasco.
